                    "company": "Gemeente Almere",
                    "description": "At the department of Almere Hout & Almere Poort I work as a Senior Urban Designer. As such I work on most of the strategic projects and complex city development projects, such as Plan Dune, Nobelhorst, the Icedome and Almere Poort East. I work in multidisciplinary teams and coordinate with the projectmanager the entire process and content. As the Lead Urban Designer of the department I also coordinate the other Urban Designers, Landscape Architectcs and Draftsmen of our department and oversee all designs and plans. \n\nSince Plan Dune started in 2008 I have been a part of it. My work on the project contains of being the coordinator for the content of the plan. For the plans of the developers Amvest and Den Daas, housing and a public harbor, I am the contact person and I guiding their unconventional plans through our municipal organization and get them realized. For the municipal parts in this plan, the beaches and the dikes, I coordinate all the designs and designers. \n\nIn Nobelhorst I design together with housing corporation Ymere the plots and the public space. Here we have introduced a new form of participation in the Netherlands, the design of the public space will be co-designed by the inhabitants.\n\nFrom 2011 till 2012 I have worked on the Werkmaatschappij Almere Centrum Weerwater, the precursor of the agricultural and horticultural exhibition Floriade, which will be hosted in Almere in 2022. With this project we entered a competition and landed the Floriade in Almere for the year 2022.\n\nBesides planning projects I spend a part of my time on more general things like the monthly presentations for the new employees of the municipality and I have been a member of the Works Council of our Municipality for 6 years.",
                    "title": "Senior Urban Planner and Designer (MSc MCD)",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
