                    "company": "Municipality of Almere",
                    "description": "At the department of Urban Design and Landscape architecture I have worked as an Urban Designer. As such I design plans on different planning levels, from regional plans, to Structure plans for the entire city and development plans for parts of the city.\n\nAt the regional level I have worked on strategic projects, such as the Atelier IJmeer and Exploration IJmeer, in which we worked closely together with the municipality of Amsterdam and the State department of Waterworks for a design of the IJmeer area. \n\nAt the level of the city my work consisted of making a Structure plan for the city of Almere, finding new strategies for differentiation in housing and housing environments, and thinking of strategies for getting a better grip on the building production, finances, quality of housing and the influence they have on each other. \n\nAt the level of development plans I designed the plan for the mixed use areas Europakwartier and Olympiakwartier and the coastal area of Almere Poort.\n\nOther projects are the experiment Simplicity, a floating housing area of five hundred houses, called Pampushaven and integrating safety into the urban designing process.\n\nBesides projects at different planning levels I spend a part of my time on more general things like the monthly presentations for the new employees of the municipality and was I coordinator for the student Atelier Almere, which hosted about fifty graduate students of the universities of Delft Eindhoven and Wageningen.",
                    "title": "Urban Planner and Designer (MSc MCD)",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
